# ddns - install to /etc/init.d/
# ddns_daemon - install to /usr/sbin
# ddns-update - install to /usr/sbin --> sends same/extended format command to send update to dns via ssh,
#    with ssh key tied to the server's /etc/ddns_update/update-client-host.sh by
#    /home/${user}/.ssh/authorized_keys file allowing that one command only
# Note: with version 0.1.0 the ssh keyid changed to id_ddns_update_46
